1
00:00:00,087 --> 00:00:00,838
In this lecture

2
00:00:01,288 --> 00:00:03,325
we will delve into the world of Docker

3
00:00:03,788 --> 00:00:05,950
a tool designed to make it easier to create

4
00:00:06,150 --> 00:00:06,800
deploy

5
00:00:06,812 --> 00:00:09,075
and run applications by using containers

6
00:00:09,463 --> 00:00:14,012
Containers allow a developer to package up an application with all of the parts it needs

7
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:16,325
such as libraries and other dependencies

8
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:18,712
and ship it all out as one package

9
00:00:19,100 --> 00:00:24,325
This ensures that the application will run on any other machine as long as it has Docker installed

10
00:00:24,725 --> 00:00:26,962
We will cover key Docker components

11
00:00:27,150 --> 00:00:28,312
including Docker Engine

12
00:00:28,587 --> 00:00:29,250
Docker Hub

13
00:00:29,525 --> 00:00:30,025
and more

